The '''Kashmir Bee Hawkmoth''' (''Hemaris rubra'') is a [[moth]] of the [[Sphingidae]] family. It is known from a number of valleys in [[Kashmir]].<ref>[http://tpittaway.tripod.com/sphinx/h_rub.htm Sphingidae of the Western Palaearctic]</ref> The habitat consists of flower-rich meadows at around 2,500 meters.

The [[wingspan]] is 44-58 mm. It is a diurnal species. Adults are wing from mid June to early August in one generation per year.

